---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="About — Roger Wibrew">
  <main class="container">
    <h1>About</h1>
    <p>
      I'm a chemical engineer with <strong>years of hands-on process experience</strong>, now combining that
      practical knowledge with <strong>machine learning</strong> and <strong>modern software tools</strong>.
      The combination matters — ML models are only as good as the domain understanding behind them, and
      I bring both.
    </p>
    <p>
      My work connects fundamental modeling (thermodynamics and system dynamics) with modern implementation
      (web apps, automation, and AI-assisted development). I focus on <strong>process simulation</strong>,
      <strong>dynamic systems</strong>, and <strong>engineering software</strong> that solves real problems.
    </p>
    <p>
      This site is a growing portfolio of technical writing and small tools that demonstrate how I approach problems:
      define assumptions clearly, build models that can be tested, and deliver outputs people can actually use.
    </p>

    <h2>Work With Me</h2>
    <p>
      I'm always open to interesting conversations — whether that's collaborating on a project,
      exploring an idea, or just talking shop about process engineering and ML.
    </p>
    <a class="work-btn" href="/contact">Get in touch &rarr;</a>
  </main>

  <style>
    .container { max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 3rem 1.25rem; }
    h1 { margin: 0 0 1.5rem; }
    p { line-height: 1.75; color: var(--text-secondary); }
    strong { color: var(--text-primary); }
    h2 { margin: 2.5rem 0 0.75rem; }
    .work-btn {
      display: inline-block;
      margin-top: 0.5rem;
      padding: 0.6rem 1.25rem;
      border-radius: 8px;
      background: var(--accent);
      color: #fff;
      text-decoration: none;
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      font-weight: 500;
      transition: background 0.15s ease;
    }
    .work-btn:hover { background: var(--accent-hover); color: #fff; }
  </style>
</Layout>
